The paper proposes a deep learning strategy for cross-domain recommendation in collaborative filtering. The main focus is on designing a neural architecture and formulating a cross-domain loss function to compute the non-linearity in user preferences across domains. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-category. Additionally, the paper deals with information retrieval (cs.IR) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) as it involves recommending items to users based on their preferences. The paper also mentions the use of natural language processing (cs.CL) and computer vision (cs.CV) in some of the domains. Therefore, these sub-categories are also likely to be relevant.
